// Adversarial: Arcwelder (TetherBeam chain mode) fires fire_chain on every Bumped event,
// which despawns all TetherChainBeam entities and rebuilds N-1 beams for N sorted bolts.
// Simultaneously, maintain_tether_chain runs every FixedUpdate tick and performs the SAME
// despawn-and-rebuild whenever the bolt count changes. Prism generates both triggers for
// this collision: it spawns an extra bolt on PerfectBump (bolt count +1, triggering
// maintain_tether_chain on the next tick) and applies TimePenalty on BoltLost (bolt count -1,
// triggering maintain_tether_chain again). The chaos input at 0.6 drives frequent Bumped
// events that re-fire fire_chain before maintain_tether_chain has resolved the previous
// rebuild. The race condition risk: if fire_chain despawns beams that maintain_tether_chain
// has already queued for respawn (or vice versa), stale TetherChainBeam entities accumulate
// (NoEntityLeaks), beam components reference despawned bolt entities causing NaN propagation
// into tick_tether_beam damage arithmetic (NoNaN), or Prism bolt-spawn accumulation under
// repeated PerfectBump fires exceeds the expected ceiling (BoltCountReasonable).
// BoltSpeedAccurate guards against speed drift from chain-mode steering interactions.
// Scatter layout varies cell spacing so tether beam path lengths differ across rebuilds,
// maximising the geometric diversity of the despawn-respawn race.
// Stress: 32 runs to explore varied RNG paths through Prism spawn and bolt-loss events.
(
    breaker: "Prism",
    layout: "Scatter",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.6)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltCountReasonable, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    invariant_params: (max_bolt_count: 12),
    allow_early_end: false,
    stress: (runs: 32, parallelism: 32),
    seed: 7211,
    chip_selections: ["Arcwelder"],
)
